captions.text:
"Quick Change", for Tomé, Elidio
and Daniel. Stand up.

I works like this:
Every time I say 'change'
they change the last thing they said.

Let's hear from that
nice couple, Vinícius and Mayan.
What do you do for a living, Mayan?

- I'm on a medical school.
- Medical school.

So give us a medical term.
Anything.

- Adenocarcinoma.
- Adeno... Cracinona... Noma!
Adenocarcinoma!

Medical "Quick Change",
starting now!
Roll call, kids!

Yay...
An apple for you, teacher!

- Thanks. Abelardo?
- Here!

- Adenocarcinoma?
- Here! Here, teacher!

Here!
Adenocarcinoma Junior!
Change!

- Adenocarcinoma II!
- Change!
Adenocarcinoma Tylenol!

- And Carlinhos?
- He didn't come, teacher!

- Teacher, I wonder why Carlinhos
misses so many classes... - Change!

- I wonder why Carlinhos never comes...
- Change!

They say Carlinhos is taking some
medicines and won't come back...

Carlinhos is grounded at home.
Oh, that big ear annoying kid...

- Geez, what did he do, teacher?
- Yeah, what did he do?

- He got born!
- Change!

- He got into my life!
- Change!

He took a crap in the classroom,
but that's not the point!

- Geez... - I crap in my living room
and my dad doesn't ground me!

- Well... - Giving you that name
is punishment enough...

- Are you saying my name
is not normal? - Change!

- Are you saying my name is weird?
- Change!

Don't you know any other
Adenocarcinoma?

Adenocarcinoma is
a totally common name!
It's a half-italian, half-arabian name!

- My student...
- Change!

- Dear!
- Change!
Ade...
What, teach?
Your name isn't actually uncommon!
It is uncommon!

- But you don't have
to feel bad for it. - Change!

- You don't have to feel
guilty about it. - Change!

You could change your name,
do you know that?

And you want to
change your name to...?
I want to change to...

That's a serious case, he's
called Elidio. But let me go first!
An improbable flashback!

Oh, Adenocarcinoma,
what a beautiful name!

- What is it?
- It's a gland tumor...

- Gland tumor...
- How beautiful! How cute!

CIA. BARBIXAS DE HUMOR
presented

IMPROVÁVEL
Probably a good show.
